name: Orderville Canyon
description:
Introduction

One of the classics in Zion. It is best done in combination with other technical canyons like Englestead Hollow, Birch Hollow and others.

Approach

Upper Orderville outside of the park boundary. At the lower 4X4 Parking.

{{#ev:vimeo|240405773}}

Descent

R1/DC is 17' with bolts RDC before the junction with Birch.

R2/DC is 20' with bolts LDC after the junction with Englestead.

Exit

Red tape

Entry to this area may be restricted; check for information regarding permits before attempting this trip
